This document is an "IBM Batch Report" dated June 15, 2016, pertaining to Electoral Event ID 19694 in NSW, specifically Batch Number 6 from the Bangor Vote Collection Point. It provides metadata including the batch creation timestamp, operator, site, workstation, and associated batch file. The core of the report details the processing status for 50 individual ballots (Ballot Numbers 1 through 50). For each ballot, the report tracks the outcome of various checks related to ballot formality and preference recording, including `QualityAssurance Checked`, `Initials Checked`, `Official Mark Checked`, `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Formality Result Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, and multiple checks for Above-the-Line (ATL) and Below-the-Line (BTL) preferences, mismatches, and formality. Most entries indicate "OK", but two instances of "HAS ISSUES" are present: for Ballot Number 10 under `UnusualMarkings Checked` and for Ballot Number 31 under `Verification Action`.

This document is highly relevant to Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] as it is a direct example of an "IBM Batch Report" from 2016, fulfilling the request for "IBM Outputs." It provides the sought-after insights into ballot processing, including comprehensive batch metadata and granular, ballot-level check statuses for formality, initials, marks, and preferences. The specific "HAS ISSUES" entries for `UnusualMarkings Checked` and `Verification Action` directly align with the FOI request's interest in identifying anomalies or exceptions within the ballot processing workflow, demonstrating the operational details and potential flags within the system.
